ascular network participates in heat/mass\ntransport operations. Further, dye flow propounds the functionality of such\ndevices. Our study hence proposes a simple and scalable hybrid microtechnolgy\nto fabricate fluidic devices having multiscale architecture. This will also\nfacilitate the rapid fabrication of microfluidic devices for biomedical,\ndiagnostics, sensors and micro-TAS applications.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 7 Apr 2017 06:59:07 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-04-10"}
